The paper deals with the problem of supporting Rank() and Select() operations on a bit vector, which are fundamental operations in data structures and algorithms. The use of the succinct index model and the focus on density-sensitive trade-offs suggest that the paper belongs to the category of data structures (cs.DS) and possibly also to the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The consideration of processing time and the use of information theory concepts suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the focus on pre-processing and the use of additional data structures suggest that the paper may also belong to the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
